'cont'=>'(JiaZi May 23), June 22, 1984, Deng Xiaoping said that Hong Kong will remain unchanged for 50 years of the implementation of \"one country, two systems\". In 22-23 June <br> 1984, Deng Xiaoping met with Sze-yuen Chung, Hong Kong businessmen to Beijing, and Hong Kong celebrities. In conversation, he said, the principles and policies of the stance taken by the Chinese government to resolve the issue of Hong Kong, is unwavering. We have said many times, the Chinese government resumed the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong in 1997, Hong Kong&#39;s current social and economic systems unchanged, laws basically unchanged, the same way, the status of Hong Kong as a free port and international trade and financial center unchanged, Hong Kong can continue to maintain and develop economic relations with other countries and regions. As we have said many times, apart from stationing troops, Beijing cadres are not sent to the Hong Kong SAR Government, and this will not change. We send troops to safeguard national security, not to interfere in the internal affairs of Hong Kong. Our policy of Hong Kong for 50 years. We say this, then it says. He said that our policy is the implementation of \"one country, two systems\", specifically, in the People&#39;s Republic of China, the mainland population of 1 billion in the socialist system, Hong Kong, Taiwan capitalist system. <br>'
